Authentication (Spring interface)
→ A Java interface used internally by Spring Security to represent the authenticated user

💡 Example

When a user logs in:

Spring creates an object of Authentication
It contains:
username
password
roles/authorities
authentication status

⚡ One line to remember:

SecurityContextHolder = place where Spring stores current user authentication details

🔥 In your JWT project:

After login:

JWT is validated
User info is stored in SecurityContextHolder
You can access user anywhere in your backend
